      "text": [
        ": مَنْ لَقِیَ أَخَاهُ بِمَا یَسُرُّهُ سَرَّهُ اللَّهُ یَوْمَ الْقِیَامَهِ وَ مَنْ لَقِیَ أَخَاهُ بِمَا یَسُوؤُهُ لِیَسُوءَهُ سَاءَهُ اللَّهُ یَوْمَ یَلْقَاهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "1. And from the previous chain from Muhammad b. Ahmad from Ahmad b. Muhammad from Nadhar b. Wakee’ from al-Rabee’ b. Sabeeh who raised this narration to The Prophet (s.a.w.s.) who said: “One who meets a believer to please him, Allah will make the former happy on the Day of Judgment. One who meets a believer to make him sad, Allah will make the former sad on the Day of Judgment.”"
        ]
      }
